                <h1>Kauai History: Discover the Garden Isle's Fascinating Past</h1>
                <p>Kauai, also known as the "Garden Isle," boasts a rich history shaped by Polynesian settlers, European explorers, and sugarcane plantations. The island was once ruled by Hawaiian kings and is dotted with ancient temples. Today, Kauai's cultural heritage is celebrated through festivals, hula, and historical sites, making it a captivating destination.</p>
